info.name: [Vendor Retail Procurement APIs] Vendor Order to Cash Automation
info.description:
Amazon provides vendors with several APIs for the Retail Procurement business program. This postman collection includes all the API operations for the Vendor Oder to Cash Automation flow.

For more information refer to [Vendor Retail Procurement APIs Use Case Guide](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/vendor-retail-procurement-apis-v1-use-case-guide).

## Workflow & Steps

- Collection Variables tab has all the required variables for the API operations. Modify them with your actual values.
    
- Call the _**Authorization API**_ to get the _**access token**_ in exchange to the refresh token. This access token is passed as a header to all the SP API calls.
    
- Note - The **POST** are asynchronous hence you need to check the **API Operation Status** for success and issues using the **get Transaction** operation.
    

1. Firstly, Fetch the pending purchase orders for fulfillment calling the **get Purchase Orders** operation. To get more information on a particular purchase order call **get Purchase Order** operation.
    
2. Then send an acknowledgement to Amazon for the order using **submitAcknowledgement** operation.
    
3. Call **get Purchase Orders Status** to get the acknowledgement status of the items in purchase orders available to you for fulfillment.
    
4. You can call **SubmitShipments** operation to submit requests for the pickup of their shipments by Amazon. **This is only applicable to Collect or WePay vendors.**
    
5. Call **GetShipmentDetails** operation to retrieve scheduled pickup and carrier assignment information. **This is only applicable to Collect or WePay vendors.**
    
6. Now call **SubmitShipmentSonfirmations** operation to submit shipment confirmations to Amazon. With your shipment confirmation Amazon can efficiently receive and process your shipments.
    
7. To request payment from Amazon for items shipped call the **submitInvoices** operation.

request.description:
Returns a list of purchase orders created or changed during the time frame that you specify. You define the time frame using the `createdAfter`, `createdBefore`, `changedAfter` and `changedBefore` parameters. The date range to search must not be more than 7 days. You can choose to get only the purchase order numbers by setting `includeDetails` to false. You can then use the `getPurchaseOrder` operation to receive details for a specific purchase order.

| 10 | 10 |
